    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-09-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-09-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="23"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d23">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/9–2650</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minute of Conversation Between the Secretary of State and the
                        British Secretary of State for Foreign Affairs</hi> (<hi rend="italic"
                        >Bevin</hi>)<note n="1" xml:id="d23fn1">Drafted by Lucius D. Battle of the
                        Executive Secretariat.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-09-26">September 26,
                            1950</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In a conversation on other matters, Mr. Bevin said that the British were very
                    much concerned about the Michael Scott Case.</p>
                <p>Mr. Acheson said that we were going into this problem very carefully and
                    mentioned the fact that the passage of the McCarran Bill somewhat complicated
                    our handling of the problem.<note n="2" xml:id="d23fn2">This refers to the
                        Internal Security Act of 1950 (64 Stat. 987), which was enacted into law by
                        the Houses of Congress over the President’s objection on September 23.
                        Documentation on the impact of this legislation on the conduct of United
                        States foreign relations is scheduled for publication in <ref
                            target="frus1950v01">volume <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>
                        </ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lucius</hi> D. <hi rend="smallcaps">Battle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
